more generic way of doing this. We pad the label with spaces on either side, and then search for " ai " to ensure we are only matching ai as a standalone token, and not as part of another word. 
We also include the full term "artificial intelligence" in case that is used as a label.

SELECT COUNT(*) AS ai_label_count
FROM (
  SELECT ' ' || lower(label) || ' ' AS padded_label
  FROM chunks
)
WHERE padded_label LIKE '% ai %'
   OR padded_label LIKE '% artificial intelligence %';

